牺牲无辜者取得的胜利  根本算不上胜利
Victory at the expense of the innocent, is no victory at all.

19:29.430 --> 19:31.310
瓦坎达国王接着...
The Wakanda King went on to...

19:31.310 --> 19:33.330
他们不受国际法的限制
They are operating outside and above the international law.

19:33.330 --> 19:37.680
如果我们不回应此类行为  就会变成这样
Because that's the reality, if we don't respond to acts like these.

19:37.680 --> 19:40.160
旺达·马克西莫夫这样的能力增强者
What legal authority does an enhanced individual

19:40.160 --> 19:43.340
有什么法律权利在尼日利亚行动
like Wanda Maximoff have to operate in Nige...

19:47.910 --> 19:50.270
-都怪我  -不是的
- It's my fault. - That's not true.

19:50.270 --> 19:53.880
那就把电视再打开  他们可指名道姓了
Then turn the TV back on, they're being very specific.

19:53.990 --> 19:55.250
我早该拆除那件炸弹背心
I should've clocked that bomb vest

19:55.270 --> 19:57.140
而不是让你不得不动手
long before you have to deal with it.

19:58.550 --> 20:00.250
朗姆洛提到"巴基"
Rumlow said 'Bucky' and...

20:01.610 --> 20:04.490
突然间  我又成了那个布鲁克林的16岁少年
All of a sudden, I was a 16 year old kid again in Brooklyn.

20:09.120 --> 20:10.210
有人死了
And people died.

20:12.860 --> 20:15.800
-这怪我  -怪我们俩
- It's on me. - It's on both of us.

20:16.900 --> 20:17.950
这份工作
This job...

20:21.450 --> 20:23.820
我们尽可能救下更多的人
We try to save as many people as we can.

20:24.370 --> 20:26.110
有时并不能救每个人
Sometimes that doesn't mean everybody,

20:26.240 --> 20:28.200
但如果我们无法接受这一点
but, if we can't find a way to live with that,

20:28.290 --> 20:29.330
下次
then next time...

20:31.490 --> 20:33.040
也许我们谁都救不了
maybe nobody get saved.

20:37.250 --> 20:39.390
小幻  我们谈过的
Vis, we talked about this.

20:39.390 --> 20:42.100
是啊  但门开着  所以我以为
Yes. But the door was opened so I assumed that...

20:44.080 --> 20:47.150
罗杰斯队长说斯塔克先生回来让我通知他
Captain Rogers wished to know when Mr. Stark was arriving.

20:47.150 --> 20:48.910
谢谢  我马上下去
Thank you. I'll be right down.

20:49.130 --> 20:51.230
我...走门
I'll... use the door.

20:52.160 --> 20:54.550
还有  他带了位客人
Oh, and apparently, he's brought a guest.

20:54.640 --> 20:55.730
你知道是谁吗
You know who it is?

20:56.590 --> 20:58.110
国务卿
The Secretary of State.

21:02.440 --> 21:05.180
五年前  我心脏病发作
5 years ago, I had a heart attack.

21:05.960 --> 21:08.790
打高尔夫球后挥杆时昏了过去
and dropped right in the middle of my backswing.

21:09.640 --> 21:11.760
结果  那成了我人生最大的幸事
Turned out, it was the best round of my life

21:11.760 --> 21:15.960
因为经历了13小时的手术和三重搭桥术之后
because after 13 hours of surgery and a triple bypass.

21:17.140 --> 21:20.920
我发现了四十年军队生涯没教过我的东西
I found something 40 years in the army never taught me:

21:21.720 --> 21:23.070
远见
perspective.

21:24.690 --> 21:28.740
全世界欠复仇者联盟一个无法偿还的人情
The world owes the Avengers an unpayable debt.

21:29.780 --> 21:32.580
你们为我们而战
You have... fought for us.

21:33.020 --> 21:36.120
保护了我们  拿生命冒险
Protected us. Risked your lives.

21:36.340 --> 21:39.800
虽然有很多人把你们当成英雄
But while a great many people see you as heroes.

21:40.380 --> 21:41.790
但也有一些人
There are some...

21:43.680 --> 21:45.600
更愿意用"义务警员"这个词
who would prefer the word "vigilantes."

21:45.600 --> 21:48.380
你会用哪个词  国务卿先生
And what word would you use, Mr. Secretary.

21:48.380 --> 21:49.900
"危险"怎么样
How about "dangerous?"

21:50.120 --> 21:55.420
你会如何形容一群驻扎在美国的能力增强者
What would you call a group of US-based, enhanced individuals,

21:55.420 --> 21:58.180
习惯性地无视主权国家边界
who routinely ignores sovereign borders

21:58.190 --> 22:01.520
去哪  做什么  全凭自己意愿
and inflict their will wherever they choose

22:01.520 --> 22:06.020
而且老实说  对造成的后果也似乎毫不关心
and who, frankly, seem unconcerned about what they leave behind.

22:10.530 --> 22:11.550
纽约
New York.

22:26.040 --> 22:27.390
华盛顿特区
Washington D.C.

22:36.270 --> 22:37.510
索科威亚
Sokovia.

22:48.490 --> 22:49.600
拉各斯
Lagos.

22:58.510 --> 23:00.320
好了  够了
Okay. That's enough.

23:02.350 --> 23:03.440
过去四年中
For the past 4 years,

23:03.450 --> 23:06.720
你们的行动拥有无限权力而且无人监管
you've operated with unlimited power and no supervision.

23:06.810 --> 23:08.860
世界各国政府对这种情况
That's an arrangement the governments of the world

23:08.860 --> 23:10.880
已不能再容忍
can no longer tolerate.

23:13.610 --> 23:15.370
但我们有解决办法
But I think we have a solution.

23:19.620 --> 23:21.640
《索科威亚协议》
The Sokovia Accords.

23:22.540 --> 23:25.530
117国批准
Approved by 117 countries.

23:25.530 --> 23:28.080
其中写明  复仇者联盟
It states, that the Avengers

23:28.130 --> 23:31.140
不再是私人组织
shall no longer be a private organization.

23:31.140 --> 23:32.320
而是
Instead,

23:32.460 --> 23:36.930
要在一个联合国小组的监督下行动
they'll operate under the supervision of a United Nations Panel,

23:36.930 --> 23:41.630
且是否出动要由该小组决定
only when and if that Panel deems it necessary.

23:42.520 --> 23:45.320
复仇者联盟的成立是为了让世界更安全
The Avengers were formed to make the world a safer place.

23:45.820 --> 23:47.180
我觉得我们做到了
I feel we've done that.

23:47.610 --> 23:51.640
队长  你知道托尔和班纳现在在哪吗
Tell me Captain, do you know where Thor and Banner are right now?

23:52.530 --> 23:55.290
我要是搞丢了两个30兆吨级的核武器
If I misplaced a couple of 30 megaton nukes,

23:55.290 --> 23:57.570
肯定会有后果
you can bet there'd be consequences.

23:58.020 --> 24:02.340
妥协  保证  世界就是这样运转的
Compromise. Reassurance. That's how the world works.

24:02.410 --> 24:05.530
相信我  这就是中间立场
Believe me, this is the middle ground.

24:06.420 --> 24:09.350
有应急预案的吧
So, there are contingencies.

24:09.350 --> 24:11.700
三天后  联合国将在维也纳召开会议
3 days from now, the UN meets in Vienna

24:11.700 --> 24:13.400
批准《协议》
to ratify the Accords.

24:16.390 --> 24:17.610
你们好好谈谈吧
Well, talk it over.

24:21.320 --> 24:24.310
要是我们的决定你不喜欢呢
And if we come to a decision you don't like?

24:25.300 --> 24:27.020
那你们就退休
Then you retire.

24:32.880 --> 24:36.900
<b>克利夫兰</b>

24:50.330 --> 24:51.340
有人吗
Hello?

24:52.960 --> 24:54.620
外面停的是你的车吗
Is this your car out front?

24:56.760 --> 24:58.280
我开到人行道上了
I jumped the kerb.

25:00.310 --> 25:03.300
也许我们可以私了
Maybe we could, take care of it ourselves.

25:03.310 --> 25:04.550
要是你想打电话叫警察
I mean, if you want to call the cops,

25:04.550 --> 25:06.070
那也可以
that...that's okay too, I guess.

25:06.070 --> 25:06.870
不
No.

25:08.850 --> 25:09.930
不用叫警察
No cops.

25:11.430 --> 25:12.280
谢谢
Thank you.

25:49.740 --> 25:51.220
你怎么没变样  上校
You kept your looks, Colonel.

25:52.460 --> 25:53.940
恭喜你
Congratulations.

25:57.340 --> 26:01.440
任务汇报  1991年12月16日
Mission report: December 16, 1991

26:01.690 --> 26:02.840
你是谁
Who are you?

26:04.080 --> 26:05.460
我叫泽莫
My name is Zemo.

26:07.230 --> 26:09.090
我会重复一遍我的问题
I will repeat my question.

26:09.950 --> 26:15.230
任务汇报  1991年12月16日
Mission report. December 16, 1991

26:15.230 --> 26:16.650
你怎么找到我的
How did you find me?

26:16.650 --> 26:18.300
神盾局陷落时
When S.H.I.E.L.D. fell,

26:19.230 --> 26:22.050
黑寡妇公布了九头蛇文件
Black Widow released Hydra files to the public.

26:22.680 --> 26:25.500
有数百万页  大都加了密
Millions of pages much of it encrypted.

26:25.510 --> 26:27.120
很难破译
Not easy to decipher.

26:27.260 --> 26:28.170
但是
But,

26:30.650 --> 26:32.160
我有经验
I have experience.

26:33.290 --> 26:34.700
也有耐心
And patience.

26:36.340 --> 26:38.620
有这两样就什么都能做成
A man can do anything if he has those.

26:39.530 --> 26:40.840
你想要什么
What do you want?

26:41.830 --> 26:47.560
任务汇报  1991年12月16日
Mission report. December 16, 1991

26:48.030 --> 26:51.130
见鬼去吧
Go to hell.

27:05.620 --> 27:08.360
九头蛇活该灰飞烟灭
Hydra deserves its place on the ashheap,

27:08.610 --> 27:10.760
所以  我不介意杀你
so your death would not bother me.

27:11.710 --> 27:13.790
但你不说  我就得用这本书
But I'd have to use this book,

27:13.930 --> 27:17.560
和其他更血腥的手段  来找到我要的
and other bloodier methods to find what I need.

27:17.560 --> 27:19.470
我并不想那样
I don't look forward to that.

27:21.200 --> 27:24.880
而你的死  也只是保住了自尊
You'd only be dying for... your pride.

27:39.900 --> 27:42.530
九头蛇万岁
Hail Hydra.

27:53.700 --> 27:56.230
国务卿罗斯有一枚国会荣誉勋章
Secretary Ross, has a Congressional Medal of Honor,

27:56.230 --> 27:57.790
比你多一枚
which is one more than you have.

27:57.790 --> 27:59.440
那么假设我们同意签字
So, let's say we agree to this thing.

27:59.440 --> 28:01.430
政府过多久就会像追踪普通罪犯那样
How long does it gonna be before they LoJack us

28:01.430 --> 28:02.540
追踪我们
like a bunch of common criminals?

28:02.540 --> 28:05.010
117个国家要签这份协议
117 countries want to sign this.

28:05.110 --> 28:06.450
117个  山姆
117, Sam,

28:06.460 --> 28:07.620
你就完全不当回事吗
and you're just like, "No, that's cool. We got it."

28:07.620 --> 28:09.030
你还要做多久两面派
How long are you gonna play both sides?

28:09.040 --> 28:11.990
-我有个方程式  -这样就明白了
- I have an equation. - Oh, this will clear it up.

28:12.710 --> 28:15.670
斯塔克先生宣布他是钢铁侠后的八年里
In the 8 years since Mr. Stark announced himself as Iron Man,

28:15.670 --> 28:20.310
能力增强者的数量一直呈指数增长
the number of known enhanced persons has grown exponentially.

28:20.370 --> 28:22.470
同一段时期里
And during the same period,

28:22.630 --> 28:24.560
可能引发世界末日的事件数量
the number of potentially world-ending events

28:24.560 --> 28:26.520
也在同时上升
has risen at a commensurate rate.

28:26.530 --> 28:28.000
你是说  这是我们的错吗
You saying it's our fault?

28:28.220 --> 28:30.340
我是说  这可能有因果关系
I'm saying there maybe a causality.

28:32.640 --> 28:35.410
我们的超能力招来挑战
Our very strength invites challenge.

28:35.410 --> 28:37.900
挑战激发冲突
Challenge incites conflict.

28:38.340 --> 28:39.470
而冲突
And conflict...

28:41.540 --> 28:43.230
会引发灾难
breeds catastrophe.

28:44.130 --> 28:45.410
监管
Oversight.

28:47.880 --> 28:50.880
是我们应该给予考虑的
Oversight is not an idea that can be dismissed out of hand.

28:50.880 --> 28:51.850
说到点上了
Boom.

28:52.310 --> 28:56.840
托尼  你安静得出奇啊
Tony, you're being uncharacteristically non-hyperverbal.

28:56.840 --> 28:58.320
因为他已经决定好了
It's because he's already made up his mind.

28:58.320 --> 28:59.730
天呐  你真懂我
Boy, you know me so well.

29:01.410 --> 29:03.850
实际上  是电磁头痛犯了
Actually, I'm nursing my electromagnetic headache.

29:04.690 --> 29:05.780
所以我才沉默  队长
That's what's going on, Cap.

29:05.780 --> 29:07.140
就是疼
It's just pain...

29:08.630 --> 29:10.130
不舒服
it's discomfort.

29:10.190 --> 29:12.640
是谁把咖啡渣倒进垃圾处理器了
Who's putting coffee grounds in the disposal?

29:12.980 --> 29:15.250
我是给机车党开了家旅馆吗
Am I running a bed and breakfast for a biker gang?

29:21.910 --> 29:23.920
那是查尔斯·斯宾塞
Oh, that's Charles Spencer by the way.

29:24.350 --> 29:26.660
是个好孩子  计算机工程专业
He's a great kid. Computer engineering degree.

29:26.660 --> 29:28.630
平均成绩3.6
3.6 GPA.

29:28.770 --> 29:31.520
计划秋天去因特尔基层上班
Had a floor-level gig at Intel planned for the fall.

29:31.640 --> 29:34.170
但是  他想趁窝在办公室里之前
But first, he wanted to put a few miles on his soul,

29:34.220 --> 29:35.900
先去积累阅历
before he park it behind a desk.

29:35.900 --> 29:38.110
看看世界  做做义工
See the world, maybe be of service.

29:39.360 --> 29:41.220
查理不想去维加斯或劳德尔堡
Charlie didn't want to go to Vegas or Fort Lauderdale

29:41.220 --> 29:42.010
要我就会选那些地方
which is what I would do.

29:42.010 --> 29:44.920
也没去巴黎或阿姆斯特丹  那儿多有趣
He didn't go to Paris or Amsterdam, which sounds fun.

29:45.250 --> 29:46.980
他想利用暑假
He decided to spend his summer,

29:47.170 --> 29:48.720
给穷人建生态住宅
building sustainable housing for the poor.

29:48.720 --> 29:50.320
猜猜是哪  索科威亚
Guess where, Sokovia.

29:54.340 --> 29:55.780
他可能是想做出些改变
He wanted to make a difference, I suppose.

29:55.780 --> 29:56.520
但我们无从得知了
I mean, we won't know

29:56.520 --> 29:57.760
因为我们打得正高兴时
cause we dropped a building on him

29:57.760 --> 29:59.510
向他身上砸了一栋楼
while we were kicking ass.

30:07.520 --> 30:09.540
我们完全没有决策程序
There's no decision making process here.

30:11.830 --> 30:13.360
我们需要受到管制
We need to be put in check.

30:13.420 --> 30:15.160
不管以什么形式  我都接受
Whatever form that takes, I'm game.

30:15.680 --> 30:17.670
如果不受限制  我们就会无法无天
If we can't accept limitations, if we're bounderless,

30:17.670 --> 30:20.050
比坏人好不到哪去
we're no better than the bad guys.

30:20.220 --> 30:22.230
托尼  有人死在你眼皮下
Tony, someone dies on your watch,

30:22.230 --> 30:22.770
你不能就此放弃
you don't give up.

30:22.770 --> 30:23.650
谁说我们要放弃了
Who said we're giving up?

30:23.650 --> 30:26.450
如果不对自己的行为负责  就是放弃
We are, for not taking responsibility for our actions.

30:26.610 --> 30:28.090
这些文件只是在推卸责任
These documents just shifts the blames.

30:28.090 --> 30:29.580
对不起  史蒂夫
I'm sorry, Steve, that...

30:30.320 --> 30:31.930
这话自负得危险
That is dangerously arrogant.

30:31.940 --> 30:33.980
这可是联合国啊
This is the United Nations we're talking about.

30:33.980 --> 30:36.550
不是世界安全理事会
It's not the World Security Council,

30:36.560 --> 30:37.920
不是神盾局  也不是九头蛇
it's not S.H.I.E.L.D., it's not Hydra.

30:37.920 --> 30:39.940
对  但管理者仍是人  人有目的
No, but it's run by people with agendas

30:39.940 --> 30:40.710
而目的会变
and agendas change.

30:40.720 --> 30:42.710
那是好事  所以我才会在这儿
That's good. That's why I'm here.

30:42.710 --> 30:44.600
当我意识到我的武器落入敌手
When I realized what my weapons were capable of

30:44.600 --> 30:45.660
后果会多不堪设想时
in the wrong hands,

30:45.690 --> 30:47.350
我就停止生产了
I shut it down, stopped manufacturing...

30:47.350 --> 30:49.770
托尼  那是你的选择
Tony. You chose to do that.

30:49.770 --> 30:52.280
如果我们签字  就放弃了选择权
If we sign this, we surrender our right to choose.

30:53.660 --> 30:56.020
如果小组派我们去不该去的地方
What if this Panel sends us somewhere we don't think we should go.

30:56.020 --> 30:58.890
或是不许我们去该去的地方呢
What if there's somewhere we need to go, and they don't let us.

30:59.010 --> 31:02.150
我们也许不完美  但仍是最可靠的人
We may not be perfect, but the safest hands are still our own.

31:02.150 --> 31:06.340
如果现在不签  将来他们会强迫我们签
If we don't do this now, it's going to be done to us later.

31:06.660 --> 31:08.210
事实就是如此  到时会闹得很不好看
That's the fact. That won't be pretty.

31:08.210 --> 31:11.340
-你是说他们会来抓我  -我们会保护你的
- You're saying they'll come for me. - We would protect you.

31:11.390 --> 31:12.820
或许托尼是对的
Maybe Tony's right.

31:14.270 --> 31:17.960
如果我们稍作妥协  就还有回旋余地
If, we have one hand on the wheel we can still steer.

31:18.720 --> 31:19.230
但如果彻底决裂...
If we take it off...

31:19.240 --> 31:20.120
你还是不是
Aren't you the same woman

31:20.120 --> 31:22.330
几年前跟政府叫板的那个女人了
who told the government to kiss her ass a few years ago?

31:22.330 --> 31:25.260
我这是...审时度势
I'm just... reading the terrain.

31:25.270 --> 31:28.620
我们在公众面前犯了些大错
We have made some very public mistakes.

31:28.740 --> 31:30.170
我们需要重获他们的信任
We need to win their trust back.

31:30.190 --> 31:30.980
慢着
Focus up.

31:30.980 --> 31:33.720
抱歉  是我听错了吗  你是在支持我吗
I'm sorry, did I just mishear you or did you agree with me.

31:33.720 --> 31:36.210
-我想反悔了  -不不  不能收回
- Oh, I want to take it back. - No, no, no. You can't retract it.

31:36.270 --> 31:38.380
谢谢啊  真是破天荒
Thank you. Unprecedented.

31:39.200 --> 31:40.560
好了  这事结了
Okay, case close.

31:40.560 --> 31:42.570
<b>她在睡梦中去世了</b>

31:40.770 --> 31:41.500
我赢了
I win.

31:43.040 --> 31:44.020
我得走了
I have to go.

31:57.240 --> 32:00.920
<b>伦敦</b>

32:19.950 --> 32:25.620
<b>玛格丽特·佩吉·卡特</b>

32:26.360 --> 32:27.460
现在
And now,

32:27.610 --> 32:30.170
我想请莎伦·卡特
I would like to invite Sharon Carter,

32:30.220 --> 32:32.290
上台说几句
to come up and say a few words.

32:45.300 --> 32:48.410
玛格丽特·卡特为人熟知的身份是神盾局创始人
Margaret Carter was known to most as a founder of S.H.I.E.L.D.

32:49.430 --> 32:51.830
